Detailed Description

cvmx_sli_mac_credit_cnt

This register contains the number of credits for the MAC port FIFOs used by the SLI. This value needs to be set before S2M traffic flow starts. A write operation to this register causes the credit counts in the SLI for the MAC ports to be reset to the value in this register if the corresponding disable bit in this register is set to 0.
